"{\"uid\": \"hngn.com-articles-261508-20240617-olympic-athlete-dies-jj-rice-diving-accident-paris-games.htm\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"A beloved Tonganathletewas killed in a fatal diving accident weeks away from hisOlympic debut.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 94, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"JJ Rice, 18, died afterdiving off a boatinto shallow water in Faleloa, Ha'apai, Saturday afternoon,Matangi Tonga OnlineandSky Newsreported, citing JJ's father, Darren Rice.\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 96, \"end\": 98, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judge\", \"score\": 0.5636213164115889, \"rank\": 0.7503619130044311, \"text\": \"JJ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judge\"}, {\"begin\": 158, \"end\": 165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faleloa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Faleloa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faleloa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faleloa\"}, {\"begin\": 167, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ha\\u02bbapai\", \"score\": 0.9963976429562891, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ha'apai\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ha\\u02bbapai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ha\\u02bbapai\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was found unresponsive on the ocean floor beneath the boat.\", \"from\": 270, \"to\": 332, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Divers' efforts to resuscitate him were unsuccessful, according to the outlets.\", \"from\": 333, \"to\": 412, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am in shock.\", \"from\": 414, \"to\": 429, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I still can not believe it, and it will take all of us who loved JJ so long to feel ok again,\\\" his sister, Lily Rice, wrote onFacebook, confirming his death over the weekend.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 537, \"end\": 541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lily_Aldrin\", \"score\": 0.9995939823799777, \"rank\": 0.00040611814117363557, \"text\": \"Lily\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lily_Aldrin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lily_Aldrin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"J was the most amazing, funny, unique person I have ever known, and I am going to miss everything about him.\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 714, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was so talented and was amazing at everything he tried.\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was an amazing kite foiler and he would have made it to the Olympics and come out with a big shiny medal and an even bigger smile.\\\"\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The last time I saw him he gave me a big hug and I wish I would have held on for longer,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 1011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"JJ was expected to represent Tonga in kite foil racing -- a combination of sailing, wakeboarding, surfing, windsurfing and paragliding -- at the Paris Olympics in July.\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1042, \"end\": 1047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tonga\", \"score\": 0.9999992343992492, \"rank\": 7.655867871669043e-07, \"text\": \"Tonga\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tonga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tonga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was born in the U.S. but raised in Tonga since he was three.\", \"from\": 1183, \"to\": 1246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1221, \"end\": 1226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tonga\", \"score\": 0.9999992343992492, \"rank\": 7.655867871669043e-07, \"text\": \"Tonga\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tonga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tonga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have lived in Tonga my whole life, I see 